title: For Sale/Trade:  Russian Made MOLOT 7.62x39 AK LNIB
postcontent: My VEPR has a 14x1 LH threaded 16.5” barrel with 7.62x39 muzzle brake screwed on . It uses any and all AK-47 mags. Comes with the: “UltiMAK Vepr II” Optic mount from Primary Arms: http://www.primaryarms.com/ultimak-vepr-ii-vepr-k-scout-mount-m3-bupper for mounting any and all optics. Using a quality Red Dot Optics allows you to co-witness with your manual sights. It has a beautiful sporter wooden stock with matching forearm, that can be easily converted to a folding or slide out stock or any other stock configuration you like. Russian Molot manufactured, and imported by FIME in Las Vegas. FIME has been importing the Arsenal rifles. All Molot VEPR made 7.62x39 AK variants are now banned on import to the USA. Only reason I'm selling this one, is I have two that are just alike. Both are “LNIB” and a coin toss picked this one to sell. The 16.5” chromed lined and Russian machine gun barrel is extremely well balanced, and shoulder's to sight level instinctively, like an extremely well balanced hunting rifle. The VEPR 7.62x39 was the base gun used in the very expensive Krebs Custom AK. I use to own that model Krebs, until I got my Molot VEPRS's. I have had them all, including Arsenal's, Krebs, etc. and these VEPR rifles are more accurate, and higher quality in build than any other AK platform that I have seen. The Molot VEPR is made from the Russian RPK machine gun, and has the RPK-style hammer forged chrome lined barrel and the RPK-style 1.5mm heavy stamped receiver. It gives the VEPR extra strength, without the extra weight of a milled receiver. You also have to consider that it has the RPKstyle reinforced trunnion block. These guns were made to shoot thousands of rounds. Seek out on the internet, the youtube video of one of these rifles in full auto, shooting so many rounds, one after another, that the front wooden forearm stock catches fire from it getting so hot, but still shooting. My price is $1100. Comes with original box and two mags. Original Red Russian mag in pic does not go with gun. Don't buy an overpriced Saiga converted AK or any lower end Romanian Wasp AK's, they will not have the quality, accuracy, built in toughness or re-sale of this VEPR rifle, and you will pay as much or more for them, and very rarely will you know the person or persons that did their conversions or head spaced the gun properly. Russians know how to make AK's they invented them. Stick with a Russian made AK- 47 or one of their variants. I am a private gun owner, and just selling off a few guns. (No Fire Sale Here, but you will save some money.) I only own and have purchased quality firearms. Because of arthritis many of my guns have never been fired.
